{"type":"message","id":"5cb16e05","parentId":"3c32f856","timestamp":"2026-06-12T02:34:38.089Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the skills config documentation and the skills CLI documentation to understand how to register plugin skills.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_9f1SJEVZqeoA0jKGu6Jk3482","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tools\\skills-config.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":21567,"output":94,"cacheRead":24448,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46109,"cost":{"input":0.0030193800000000003,"output":0.000026320000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0006845439999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003730244}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781231676413,"responseId":"05433951-c26e-4ad6-b5a7-c71effb4ea5a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b20430b","parentId":"5cb16e05","timestamp":"2026-06-12T02:34:38.110Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_9f1SJEVZqeoA0jKGu6Jk3482","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Skills config schema and examples\"\nread_when:\n  - Adding or modifying skills config\n  - Adjusting bundled allowlist or install behavior\ntitle: \"Skills config\"\n---\n\nMost skills loader/install configuration lives under `skills` in\n`~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`. Agent-specific skill visibility lives under\n`agents.defaults.skills` and `agents.list[].skills`.\n\n```json5\n{\n  skills: {\n    allowBundled: [\"gemini\", \"peekaboo\"],\n    load: {\n      extraDirs: [\"~/Projects/agent-scripts/skills\", \"~/Projects/oss/some-skill-pack/skills\"],\n      watch: true,\n      watchDebounceMs: 250,\n    },\n    install: {\n      preferBrew: true,\n      nodeManager: \"npm\", // npm | pnpm | yarn | bun (Gateway runtime still Node; bun not recommended)\n    },\n    entries: {\n      \"image-lab\": {\n        enabled: true,\n        apiKey: { source: \"env\", provider: \"default\", id: \"GEMINI_API_KEY\" }, // or plaintext string\n        env: {\n          GEMINI_API_KEY: \"***\",\n        },\n      },\n      peekaboo: { enabled: true },\n      sag: { enabled: false },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nFor built-in image generation/editing, prefer `agents.defaults.imageGenerationModel`\nplus the core `image_generate` tool. `skills.entries.*` is only for custom or\nthird-party skill workflows.\n\nIf you select a specific image provider/model, also configure that provider's\nauth/API key. Typical examples: `GEMINI_API_KEY` or `GOOGLE_API_KEY` for\n`google/*`, `OPENAI_API_KEY` for `openai/*`, and `FAL_KEY` for `fal/*`.\n\nExamples:\n\n- Native Nano Banana Pro-style setup: `agents.defaults.imageGenerationModel.primary: \"google/gemini-3-pro-image-preview\"`\n- Native fal setup: `agents.defaults.imageGenerationModel.primary: \"fal/fal-ai/flux/dev\"`\n\n## Agent skill allowlists\n\nUse agent config when you want the same machine/workspace skill roots, but a\ndifferent visible skill set per agent.\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    defaults: {\n      skills: [\"github\", \"weather\"],\n    },\n    list: [\n      { id: \"writer\" }, // inherits defaults -> github, weather\n      { id: \"docs\", skills: [\"docs-search\"] }, // replaces defaults\n      { id: \"locked-down\", skills: [] }, // no skills\n    ],\n  },\n}\n```\n\nRules:\n\n- `agents.defaults.skills`: shared baseline allowlist for agents that omit\n  `agents.list[].skills`.\n- Omit `agents.defaults.skills` to leave skills unrestricted by default.\n- `agents.list[].skills`: explicit final skill set for that agent; it does not\n  merge with defaults.\n- `agents.list[].skills: []`: expose no skills for that agent.\n\n## Fields\n\n- Built-in skill roots always include `~/.openclaw/skills`, `~/.agents/skills`,\n  `<workspace>/.agents/skills`, and `<workspace>/skills`.\n- `allowBundled`: optional allowlist for **bundled** skills only. When set, only\n  bundled skills in the list are eligible (managed, agent, and workspace skills unaffected).\n- `load.extraDirs`: additional skill directories to scan (lowest precedence).\n- `load.watch`: watch skill folders and refresh the skills snapshot (default: true).\n- `load.watchDebounceMs`: debounce for skill watcher events in milliseconds (default: 250).\n- `install.preferBrew`: prefer brew installers when available (default: true).\n- `install.nodeManager`: node installer preference (`npm` | `pnpm` | `yarn` | `bun`, default: npm).\n  This only affects **skill installs**; the Gateway runtime should still be Node\n  (Bun not recommended for WhatsApp/Telegram).\n  - `openclaw setup --node-manager` is narrower and currently accepts `npm`,\n    `pnpm`, or `bun`. Set `skills.install.nodeManager: \"yarn\"` manually if you\n    want Yarn-backed skill installs.\n- `entries.<skillKey>`: per-skill overrides.\n- `agents.defaults.skills`: optional default skill allowlist inherited by agents\n  that omit `agents.list[].skills`.\n- `agents.list[].skills`: optional per-agent final skill allowlist; explicit\n  lists replace inherited defaults instead of merging.\n\nPer-skill fields:\n\n- `enabled`: set `false` to disable a skill even if it’s bundled/installed.\n- `env`: environment variables injected for the agent run (only if not already set).\n- `apiKey`: optional convenience for skills that declare a primary env var.\n  Supports plaintext string or SecretRef object (`{ source, provider, id }`).\n\n## Notes\n\n- Keys under `entries` map to the skill name by default. If a skill defines\n  `metadata.openclaw.skillKey`, use that key instead.\n- Load precedence is `<workspace>/skills` → `<workspace>/.agents/skills` →\n  `~/.agents/skills` → `~/.openclaw/skills` → bundled skills →\n  `skills.load.extraDirs`.\n- Changes to skills are picked up on the next agent turn when the watcher is enabled.\n\n### Sandboxed skills + env vars\n\nWhen a session is **sandboxed**, skill processes run inside the configured\nsandbox backend. The sandbox does **not** inherit the host `process.env`.\n\nUse one of:\n\n- `agents.defaults.sandbox.docker.env` for the Docker backend (or per-agent `agents.list[].sandbox.docker.env`)\n- bake the env into your custom sandbox image or remote sandbox environment\n\nGlobal `env` and `skills.entries.<skill>.env/apiKey` apply to **host** runs only.\n\n## Related\n\n- [Skills](/tools/skills)\n- [Creating skills](/tools/creating-skills)\n- [Slash commands](/tools/slash-commands)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1781231678110}}
{"type":"message","id":"13b86f6f","parentId":"5b20430b","timestamp":"2026-06-12T02:34:42.670Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand. The plugin skills are in `plugin-skills/` directory, but they're not being loaded. According to the docs:\n\n- Built-in skill roots include `~/.openclaw/skills`, `~/.agents/skills`, `<workspace>/.agents/skills`, and `<workspace>/skills`\n- `skills.load.extraDirs` can add additional directories\n\nBut the skills are in `~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/` (which is `C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\`). This directory doesn't appear to be one of the built-in skill roots.\n\nHowever, the fact that 4 of the 6 skills in `plugin-skills/` (feishu-*) are showing up as loaded suggests that the feishu plugin provides those via the feishu channel plugin itself, not via the plugin-skills directory.\n\nThe skills that are NOT showing up are:\n1. `gitlab-permission` - GitLab permission management\n2. `memory-keeper` - Memory keeper\n3. `solo-config-field` - Solo config field management\n4. `tapd-bug-create` - TAPD bug creation\n5. `tapd-vsmode-story` - TAPD VS mode story\n6. `update-server` - Server update\n\nThese are in `plugin-skills/` but they need to be registered in the OpenClaw config. They need to be added either as `skills.load.extraDirs` or each individually.\n\nLet me check where the config file is and how to add these skills.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_06igt5z6H3G1A9XROhrx0230","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 200"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_01_vzW2EuXIMe2FeblInVl40293","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\config.* -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1