{"type":"message","id":"a089a1eb","parentId":"33259252","timestamp":"2026-06-12T02:36:36.713Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full config. I need to add the `skills.load.extraDirs` to include the `plugin-skills` directory, and also add entries for each skill to enable them.\n\nLet me add:\n1. `skills.load.extraDirs` pointing to `~/.openclaw/plugin-skills`\n2. `skills.entries` for each skill to enable them\n\nActually, looking at the docs again, if I add `extraDirs` pointing to `~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/`, the skills should be auto-discovered. But I might also need to add entries for each to make them visible. Let me try adding the extraDirs first and see.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the docs:\n\n> Built-in skill roots always include `~/.openclaw/skills`, `~/.agents/skills`, `<workspace>/.agents/skills`, and `<workspace>/skills`.\n> `load.extraDirs`: additional skill directories to scan (lowest precedence).\n\nSo if I add `~/.openclaw/plugin-skills` as an extraDir, the skills should be discovered automatically.\n\nBut I also need to make sure the skills are visible for agents. Looking at the `agents.defaults.skills` - it's not set, so skills are unrestricted by default. That should be fine.\n\nLet me add the skills config.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"现在把 plugin-skills 注册到配置里。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_sY4dbGwUdL5o7l5InRla5642","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json","edits":[{"oldText":"  \"skills\": {\n    \"allowBundled\": [\n      \"skill-creator\",\n      \"taskflow\",\n      \"taskflow-inbox-triage\"\n    ]\n  },","newText":"  \"skills\": {\n    \"allowBundled\": [\n      \"skill-creator\",\n      \"taskflow\",\n      \"taskflow-inbox-triage\"\n    ],\n    \"load\": {\n      \"extraDirs\": [\n        \"~/.openclaw/plugin-skills\"\n      ],\n      \"watch\": true\n    },\n    \"entries\": {\n      \"updat