{"type":"message","id":"88f2299d","parentId":"38d01670","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:15:56.484Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_01_o57JR5L281Uuts1Tqdwq5281","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"go weiqi baduk photo stone counting opencv python\",\n  \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1221,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9a17f69a78eb6e9a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAutomatic Go-Board Image Recognition (Weiqi, Baduk)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9a17f69a78eb6e9a\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.remi-coulom.fr/kifu-snap/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b7ff9e7ca24f1d71\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSource Code igoki, by Deon Moolman. Photo Kifu, iPhone app, by François Beaussier. Kifu, by Jim Snavely go -tracer (source code, by Sjoerd Visscher and Remco Veldkamp) Rocamgo, by Víctor Ramirez de la Corte and David Medina Velasco, in python with opencv . Imago, by Tomáš Musil (github) GBR by Sergey \\\"kol\\\" Kolchin watchGo by Daniel Bandstra img2sgf Goban Watcher kifu, by Mike Plotz Sage ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b7ff9e7ca24f1d71\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.remi-coulom.fr\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b814df3eafe946d8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nkaya-go/kaya: Play, study, and analyze Go - GitHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b814df3eafe946d8\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/kaya-go/kaya\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"23a3c25673fe6a71\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nPlay, study, and analyze Go — right from your browser or desktop. Kaya is a free, open-source Go ( Baduk / Weiqi ) application with AI-powered analysis, board recognition from photos , and a beautiful modern interface. Available on Windows, macOS, Linux, and the Web.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"23a3c25673fe6a71\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"06b941d3e8ba285e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSente is an open source python library for the game of Go\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"06b941d3e8ba285e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/atw1020/sente\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e53aa5ffe846e53d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSente (from the Japanese せんて/先手) is a general-purpose open-source python library for the ancient chinese board game Go /Badok/ Weiqi . It allows for python code to simulate and play a game of Go and also read, edit and create SGF files.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e53aa5ffe846e53d\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3acd6b435a7cd67c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSabaki — An elegant Go board and SGF editor for a more civilized age\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3acd6b435a7cd67c\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://sabaki.yichuanshen.de/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a72a7ea554c5d694\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSabaki is a modern, elegant, cross-platform Go / Baduk / Weiqi board and SGF editor for a more civilized age. It's free, open source and uses web technology based on Electron.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a72a7ea554c5d694\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"sabaki.yichuanshen.de\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d561988166d716ed\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNewest 'baduk' Questions - Stack Overflow\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d561988166d716ed\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/baduk?tab=Newest\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e4daf6535662c614\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\npython go board game, struggling to figure out how to capture multiple stones I've been trying to make a board game of GO , in python with pygame and a numpy array for storing the board locations and stone colors (0, 1, 2).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e4daf6535662c614\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"stackoverflow.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"go weiqi baduk photo stone counting opencv python","provider":"duckduckgo","count":5,"tookMs":1221,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"duckduckgo","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9a17f69a78eb6e9a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAutomatic Go-Board Image Recognition (Weiqi, Baduk)\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9a17f69a78eb6e9a\">>>","url":"https://www.remi-coulom.fr/kifu-snap/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b7ff9e7ca24f1d71\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSource Code igoki, by Deon Moolman. Photo Kifu, iPhone app, by François Beaussier. Kifu, by Jim Snavely go -tracer (source code, by Sjoerd Visscher and Remco Veldkamp) Rocamgo, by Víctor Ramirez de la Corte and David Medina Velasco, in python with opencv . Imago, by Tomáš Musil (github) GBR by Sergey \"kol\" Kolchin watchGo by Daniel Bandstra img2sgf Goban Watcher kifu, by Mike Plotz Sage ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b7ff9e7ca24f1d71\">>>","siteName":"www.remi-coulom.fr"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b814df3eafe946d8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nkaya-go/kaya: Play, study, and analyze Go - GitHub\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b814df3eafe946d8\">>>","url":"https://github.com/kaya-go/kaya","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"23a3c25673fe6a71\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nPlay, study, and analyze Go — right from your browser or desktop. Kaya is a free, open-source Go ( Baduk / Weiqi ) application with AI-powered analysis, board recognition from photos , and a beautiful modern interface. Available on Windows, macOS, Linux, and the Web.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"23a3c25673fe6a71\">>>","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"06b941d3e8ba285e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSente is an open source python library for the game of Go\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"06b941d3e8ba285e\">>>","url":"https://github.com/atw1020/sente","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e53aa5ffe846e53d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSente (from the Japanese せんて/先手) is a general-purpose open-source python library for the ancient chinese board game Go /Badok/ Weiqi . It allows for python code to simulate and play a game of Go and also read, edit and create SGF files.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e53aa5ffe846e53d\">>>","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3acd6b435a7cd67c\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSabaki — An elegant Go board and SGF editor for a more civilized age\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3acd6b435a7cd67c\">>>","url":"https://sabaki.yichuanshen.de/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a72a7ea554c5d694\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSabaki is a modern, elegant, cross-platform Go / Baduk / Weiqi board and SGF editor for a more civilized age. It's free, open source and uses web technology based on Electron.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a72a7ea554c5d694\">>>","siteName":"sabaki.yichuanshen.de"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d561988166d716ed\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nNewest 'baduk' Questions - Stack Overflow\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d561988166d716ed\">>>","url":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/baduk?tab=Newest","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e4daf6535662c614\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n