{"type":"message","id":"515aa8c5","parentId":"06e56ce6","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:16:47.934Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user sent me GitHub session cookies. They want me to use these to authenticate with GitHub and create a repository. I can use these cookies to authenticate via the browser-based approach with Playwright, or I could also try to use the GitHub API with the session cookie.\n\nActually, a simpler approach would be to save these cookies to a file and use `gh auth login` with the cookies, or use them directly to interact with the GitHub API.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. The user's GitHub username is \"yoshikun\" (from the `dotcom_user` cookie).\n\nI can:\n1. Save the cookies to a file\n2. Use Playwright to automate GitHub with these cookies to create a repo and push code\n\nOr even simpler - I could try to use the GitHub API with the session cookie (_gh_sess) to create a repo and push.\n\nActually, let me think about what to back up first. The user wants me to:\n1. Create a GitHub repo called \"OpenClaw\"\n2. Upload skills, memory, workflow, etc.\n3. Make it replicable on another computer\n\nI should save these cookies, then use them to:\n1. Create a repo via API or gh CLI\n2. Set up git in the workspace\n3. Create a proper backup structure\n4. Push everything\n\nLet me save the cookies first. But wait - I should be careful with these session cookies. They're sensitive data. Let me save them to a file that won't be committed.\n\nActually, for GitHub authentication, the simplest approach is to use these cookies with Playwright (browser automation) or directly with the gh CLI. But gh CLI needs OAuth tokens, not session cookies.\n\nLet me try a different approach - I'll use the GitHub API directly with the session cookie for authentication.\n\nActually, the most practical approach:\n1. Save cookies to a temp file\n2. Use the GitHub API to create a repo (using the session cookie or token)\n3. Initialize git in the workspace\n4. Prepare and push the backup\n\nLet me start by saving the cookies and creating the repo.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_CkS70KJkBjtvy3Q10l7Q5415","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\github_cookies.json","content":"[\n {\n \"domain\": \"github.com\",\n \"expirationDate\": 1782443731.038824,\n \"hostOnly\": true,\n \"httpOnly\": true,\n \"name\": \"__Host-user_session_same_site\",\n \"path\": \"/\",\n \"sameSite\": \"strict\",\n \"secure\": true,\n \"session\": false,\n \"storeId\": null,\n \"value\": \"S578GzfeZWxUXIfliFc59UinhZ--wJF_Sd-Kv1vg9SFWbEHE\"\n },\n {\n \"domain\": \".github.com\",\n \"expirationDate\": 1812592608.615107,\n \"hostOnly\": false,\n \"httpOnly\": true,\n \"name\": \"dotcom_user\",\n \"path\": \"/\",\n \"sameSite\": \"lax\",\n \"secure\": true,\n \"session\": false,\n \"storeId\": null,\n \"value\": \"yoshikun\"\n },\n {\n \"domain\": \".github.com\",\n \"hostOnly\": false,\n \"httpOnly\": false,\n \"name\": \"cpu_bucket\",\n \"path\": \"/\",\n \"sameSite\": \"lax\",\n \"secure\": true,\n \"session\": true,\n \"storeId\": null,\n \"value\": \"xlg\"\n },\n {\n \"domain\": \"github.com\",\n \"expirationDate\": 1788832608.61487,\n \"hostOnly\": true,\n \"httpOnly\": true,\n \"name\": \"saved_user_sessions\",\n \"path\": \"/\",\n \"sameSite\": \"lax\",\n \"secure\": true,\n \"session\": false,\n \"storeId\": null,\n \"value\": \"3197667%3AS578GzfeZWxUXIfliFc59UinhZ--wJF_Sd-Kv1vg9SFWbEHE\"\n },\n {\n \"domain\": \"github.com\",\n \"expirationDate\": 1812766564.485162,\n \"hostOnly\": true,\n \"httpOnly\": true,\n \"name\": \"_device_id\",\n \"path\": \"/\",\n \"sameSite\": \"lax\",\n \"secure\": true,\n \"session\": false,\n \"storeId\": null,\n \"value\": \"52a9e2449e90382179c2ef699b1e0b4e\"\n },\n {\n \"domain\": \"github.com\",\n \"hostOnly\": true,\n \"httpOnly\": true,\n \"name\": \"_gh_sess\",\n \"path\": \"/\",\n \"sameS