{"type":"message","id":"d41fac23","parentId":"72743baf","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:16:53.266Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to:\n1. Create a GitHub repo using the GitHub API with the session cookie\n2. Then set up the backup structure\n3. Push everything\n\nLet me first create the repo via the GitHub API. I'll extract the session cookie value from the cookies.\n\nActually, let me try using `gh auth login` approach first. No wait, gh CLI uses its own auth system, not browser cookies.\n\nLet me use the GitHub API directly. I need to get the user's info first and create a repo.\n\nThe key cookies for API auth:\n- `_gh_sess` - the main session cookie\n- `user_session` - the user session\n- `dotcom_user` = \"yoshikun\"\n\nLet me use node.js with fetch to create the repo.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_AU5sXOBjoYCOCW9PpdRh4476","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node -e \"\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\github_cookies.json', 'utf8'));\n\n// Build cookie string for API\nconst cookieStr = cookies.filter(c => !c.session).map(c => c.name + '=' + c.value).join('; ');\n\nasync function main() {\n  // Check current user\n  const userRes = await fetch('https://api.github.com/user', {\n    headers: { 'Cookie': cookieStr, 'Accept': 'application/json', 'User-Agent': 'OpenClaw' }\n  });\n  const user = await userRes.json();\n  console.log('User:', JSON.stringify(user, null, 2));\n\n  // Create repo\n  const createRes = await fetch('https://api.github.com/user/repos', {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: { 'Cookie': cookieStr, 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Accept': 'application/json', 'User-Agent': 'OpenClaw' },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      name: 'OpenClaw',\n      description: 'OpenClaw agent backup - skills, memory, workflow & config',\n      private: false,\n      auto_init: true\n    })\n  });\n  const repo = await createRes.json();\n  console.log('Repo result:', JSON.stringify(repo, null, 2));\n}\nmain().catch(e => console.error(e));\n\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":127,"output":540,"cacheRead":58368,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59035,"cost":{"input":0.000017780000000000003,"output":0.00015120000000000002,"cacheRead":0.001634304,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001803284}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781234208038,"responseId":"cf336774-33ac-4708-8967-ae2288a3a7ce"}}
