{"type":"message","id":"0b029b64","parentId":"9de46ba4","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:17:09.136Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session cookie approach doesn't work with the GitHub API directly. The API requires token-based authentication, not session cookies. I need to use a different approach.\n\nLet me try to use the GitHub API with a Personal Access Token, or use `gh auth login` with a token. Actually, let me check if there's a way to create a token via the session.\n\nAlternatively, I could try using `gh auth login` with the `--with-token` option if the user can provide a token. Or I could try to use the cookies with a browser automation (Playwright) to create a token.\n\nActually, the user gave me cookies. They probably expect me to use these with a browser (Playwright) to do things on GitHub. Let me check if Playwright is available.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_8roFmV5H3qGdUkpGXCtt6683","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node -e \"try{require('playwright');console.log('playwright available')}catch(e){console.log('not found')}\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":151,"output":249,"cacheRead":60032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60432,"cost":{"input":0.00002114,"output":0.00006972,"cacheRead":0.0016808959999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0017717559999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781234225993,"responseId":"8f189288-b7e4-4652-8615-31d2569ede32"}}
