{"type":"message","id":"53415f29","parentId":"932b7a24","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:17:14.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Playwright is not available either. Let me think of another approach. I could:\n\n1. Ask the user to create a GitHub Personal Access Token (PAT) for me\n2. Use `gh auth login --with-token` with a PAT\n3. Try using the GitHub API with a different auth approach\n\nActually, the simplest approach would be to ask the user to create a PAT with repo scope on GitHub and paste it here. Or... let me try to use the GitHub CLI with the session stored in a different way.\n\nWait, I can try a different approach - use the `gh` CLI with the token flow. Or I could try to programmatically use the GitHub session cookies to make a token.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach. I can try to authenticate gh CLI using the environment by setting GH_TOKEN or using the GITHUB_TOKEN pattern. But the user doesn't have a token.\n\nLet me ask the user to create a Personal Access Token.\n\nActually, let me try one more thing - the GitHub CLI might be able to use the web browser flow. But since gh auth status says we're not logged in, let me see if there's a way to login with the cookies.\n\nHmm, actually the user might be able to create a PAT quickly. Let me ask.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Cookie 不能直接用于 API 认证（GitHub API 要求 token 而不是 session cookie）。我可以用两种方式继续：\n\n**方式一：** 你打开 https://github.com/settings/tokens 创建一个 **经典 token**，勾上 `repo` 权限，粘贴给我就行。\n\n**方式二：** 你本地跑一下 `gh auth login`，之后我就能直接用 gh 命令操作。\n\n哪个方便？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":30,"output":355,"cacheRead":60416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60801,"cost":{"input":0.0000042000000000000004,"output":0.0000994,"cacheRead":0.001691648,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001795248}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781234229348,"responseId":"c3d78833-ed8c-4631-b682-f2660f1b49aa"}