{"type":"message","id":"c64102de","parentId":"e961b743","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:18:30.411Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The token doesn't have permission to create a repository. This is a limited PAT. Let me check what scopes it has, and if we can at least push to an existing repo.\n\nActually, looking at the error \"Resource not accessible by personal access token (createRepository)\", it means the token doesn't have the necessary scope. The token is a `github_pat_...` which is a fine-grained PAT, not a classic token. Fine-grained PATs need specific repository access and permissions.\n\nLet me check what permissions this token has, and also see if maybe we need a different approach. Maybe I can just use the API directly with this token to see what scopes/permissions it has.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_lkoOC7IUA5yZ4P9HshQb9780","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gh api user --jq '.login' 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":126,"output":214,"cacheRead":61440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61780,"cost":{"input":0.00001764,"output":0.00005992,"cacheRead":0.00172032,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00179788}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781234307311,"responseId":"c33166e2-50e7-4b7f-8fb6-89d7f8f34391"}}
