{"type":"message","id":"1a9a5089","parentId":"6fd792b0","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:50:37.684Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to set up the git remote so that push works without authentication prompts. I'll configure the credential.helper or store the remote URL with the token embedded. Actually, for a cron job that runs daily, I should set up a credential helper so the token doesn't need to be in the script.\n\nLet me configure git to use the stored token for push. I'll use git's credential store for this repo.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_vMWAN9xIMg0kSNT9hT7l6238","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\OpenClaw\"\n# configure git for this repo to remember credentials\ngit config credential.helper manager\ngit remote set-url origin https://github.com/yoshikun/OpenClaw.git\n# store the credential\n$pass = \"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\"\n@\"\nhttps://yoshikun:`$(echo $pass)@github.com\n\"@ | git credential approve 2>&1\nWrite-Host \"Git credential configured\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":112,"output":279,"cacheRead":98816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99207,"cost":{"input":0.000015680000000000002,"output":0.00007812,"cacheRead":0.002766848,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0028606480000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781236233918,"responseId":"b29fecbd-7dfd-425c-95cc-3ccecc9a18d6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e327292c","parentId":"1a9a5089","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:50:38.081Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_vMWAN9xIMg0kSNT9hT7l6238","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"git : warning: invalid credential line: https://yoshikun:$(echo ghp_VJ…Jj8v)@github.com\r\n所在位置 行:9 字符: 6\r\n+ \"@ | git credential approve 2>&1\r\n+      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: (warning: invali...j8v)@github.com:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\nfatal: unable to read credential from stdin\r\nGit credential configured"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":374,"aggregated":"git : warning: invalid credential line: https://yoshikun:$(echo 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)@github.com\r\n所在位置 行:9 字符: 6\r\n+ \"@ | git credential approve 2>&1\r\n+      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: (warning: invali...j8v)@github.com:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\nfatal: unable to read credential from stdin\r\nGit credential configured","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781236238080}}
{"type":"message","id":"13b2077b","parentId":"e327292c","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:50:42.471Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The credential helper approach isn't working well in PowerShell due to escaping issues. Let me use a different approach - store the credential in the remote URL directly (git can handle it) or use a `.git-credentials` file. But actually, putting the token in the URL in the git config isn't ideal.\n\nA better approach: I'll use `git config credential.helper store` to store the credentials, then use `git push` which will read from the store.\n\nActually, let me just use the credential.manager approach properly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_whufdAHI7jFWTNSf9par7307","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\OpenClaw\"\n# Remove any previous credential config\ngit config --unset credential.helper 2>$null\n\n# Use store helper with a targeted file\ngit config credential.helper store --file \"$(pwd)\\.git-creds\"\n\n# Write credentials\necho \"https://yoshikun: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@github.com\" | Out-File -Encoding ascii \"$(pwd)\\.git-creds\"\n\n# Secure the file\n$acl = Get-Acl \"$(pwd)\\.git-creds\"\n$acl.SetAccessRuleProtection($true, $true)\nSet-Acl \"$(pwd)\\.git-creds\" $acl\n\n# Test push (no-op since no changes)\ngit push --dry-run 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":164,"output":370,"cacheRead":99200,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99734,"cost":{"input":0.00002296,"output":0.00010360000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0027776,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00290416}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781236238082,"responseId":"b484e989-aae5-4b8b-a362-7339766a9800"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4f00f994","parentId":"13b2077b","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:50:43.113Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_whufdAHI7jFWTNSf9par7307","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"error: no action specified\ngit : fatal: The current branch master has no upstream branch.\r\n所在位置 行:17 字符: 1\r\n+ git push --dry-run 2>&1\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: (fatal: The curr...pstream branch.:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\nTo push the current branch and set the remote as upstream, use\r\n    git push --set-upstream origin master\r\nTo have this happen automatically for branches without a tracking\r\nupstream, see 'push.autoSetupRemote' in 'git help config'.\n\n(Command exited with code 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":1,"durationMs":624,"aggregated":"error: no action specified\ngit : fatal: The current branch master has no upstream branch.\r\n所在位置 行:17 字符: 1\r\n+ git push --dry-run 2>&1\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: (fatal: The curr...pstream branch.:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\nTo push the current branch and set the remote as upstream, use\r\n    git push --set-upstream origin master\r\nTo have this happen automatically for branches without a tracking\r\nupstream, see 'push.autoSetupRemote' in 'git help config'.\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781236243113}}
{"type":"message","id":"59d40495","parentId":"4f00f994","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:50:45.558Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to set the upstream branch and also ensure .git-creds is in .gitignore. Let me set these up.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_zkswbjaph5K0TEJ5ZK0x5304","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\OpenClaw\"\n# Set upstream\ngit branch --set-upstream-to=origin/master master 2>&1\n# Add creds file to gitignore\nAdd-Content .gitignore \"`n.git-creds\"\n# Test push\ngit push --dry-run 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":193,"output":162,"cacheRead":99712,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100067,"cost":{"input":0.000027020000000000002,"output":0.000045360000000000006,"cacheRead":0.002791936,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002864316}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781236243114,"responseId":"fdf9d356-626c-4388-b2c2-3dce4531cb2c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"41affd24","parentId":"59d40495","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:50:45.866Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_zkswbjaph5K0TEJ5ZK0x5304","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"git : fatal: the requested upstream branch 'origin/master' does not exist\r\n所在位置 行:3 字符: 1\r\n+ git branch --set-upstream-to=origin/master master 2>&1\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: (fatal: the requ... does not exist:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\nhint:\r\nhint: If you are planning on basing your work on an upstream\r\nhint: branch that already exists at the remote, you may need to\r\nhint: run \"git fetch\" to retrieve it.\r\nhint:\r\nhint: If you are planning to push out a new local branch that\r\nhint: will track its remote counterpart, you may want to use\r\nhint: \"git push -u\" to set the upstream config as you push.\r\nhint: Disable this message with \"git config set advice.setUpstreamFailure false\"\r\ngit : fatal: The current branch master has no upstream branch.\r\n所在位置 行:7 字符: 1\r\n+ git push --dry-run 2>&1\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: (fatal: The curr...pstream branch.:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\nTo push the current branch and set the remote as upstream, use\r\n    git push --set-upstream origin master\r\nTo have this happen automatically for branches without a tracking\r\nupstream, see 'push.autoSetupRemote' in 'git help config'.\n\n(Command exited with code 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":1,"durationMs":290,"aggregated":"git : fatal: the requested upstream branch 'origin/master' does not exist\r\n所在位置 行:3 字符: 1\r\n+ git branch --set-upstream-to=origin/master master 2>&1\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: (fatal: the requ... does not exist:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\nhint:\r\nhint: If you are planning on basing your work on an upstream\r\nhint: branch that already exists at the remote, you may need to\r\nhint: run \"git fetch\" to retrieve it.\r\nhint:\r\nhint: If you are planning to push out a new local branch that\r\nhint: will track its remote counterpart, you may want to use\r\nhint: \"git push -u\" to set the upstream config as you push.\r\nhint: Disable this message with \"git config set advice.setUpstreamFailure false\"\r\ngit : fatal: The current branch master has no upstream branch.\r\n所在位置 行:7 字符: 1\r\n+ git push --dry-run 2>&1\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: (fatal: The curr...pstream branch.:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\nTo push the current branch and set the remote as upstream, use\r\n    git push --set-upstream origin master\r\nTo have this happen automatically for branches without a tracking\r\nupstream, see 'push.autoSetupRemote' in 'git help config'.\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781236245866}}
{"type":"message","id":"02c10671","parentId":"41affd24","timestamp":"2026-06-12T03:50:48.424Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that we cloned an empty repo and then pushed via a direct URL (not through the remote). So the local repo doesn't have an upstream configured. Let me fix this by fetching first and setting up tracking properly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_YKIMspj205fTxEsoSZSY2068","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\OpenClaw\"\n# Fetch from remote\ngit fetch origin 2>&1\n# Push with -u to set upstream\ngit push -u origin master 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":496,"output":159,"cacheRead":99968,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100623,"cost":{"input":0.00006944,"output":0.00004452,"cacheRead":0.0027991039999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002913064}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781236245868,"responseId":"0f8872a9-806b-4f67-8046-783448878ccc"}}
